labelsdict = {0:'Red', 1:'Yellow', 2:'Green', 3:'No Traffic Light'}
In [5]:
def predict_signal(image):
    imgdisp = mpimg.imread(image)
    plt.imshow(imgdisp)
    imgpred = imgdisp.reshape((1,imgdisp.shape[0], imgdisp.shape[1], imgdisp.shape[2]))
    classpred = model.predict_classes(imgpred)
    print('Predicted traffic light: ', labelsdict[classpred[0]])
    return

In [4]:
# Additional line to reduce the size of the images
def to_array(images):
    img_array = []
    for each in images:
        img = mpimg.imread(each)
        #img = cv2.resize(img,(240,180))
        img_array.append(img)
    img_array = np.array(img_array)
    return img_array
In [5]:

yellows = to_array(yellowsimg)
greens = to_array(greensimg)
unknowns = to_array(unknownsimg)
